        &lt;Route path = &quot;/about&quot; component = {About}/&gt;
        &lt;Route path = &quot;/event&quot; component = {Event}/&gt;
        &lt;Route path = &quot;/qna&quot; component = {QnA}/&gt;
        &lt;Route path = &quot;/login&quot; component = {Login}/&gt;
        &lt;Route path = &quot;/join&quot; component = {Join}/&gt;
        &lt;Route path = &quot;/product&quot; component = {Product}/&gt;
        &lt;Route component={NoMatch} /&gt;
    &lt;/Switch&gt;

Obviously you&#39;d change the &lt;code&gt;NoMatch&lt;/code&gt; component with whatever you&#39;d want your default component to be.

With react-router v4, you can handle 404&#39;s in two ways:

1. Keep the path and show 404 page:

```js
&lt;Switch&gt;
    &lt;Route exact path=&quot;/&quot; component={MyComponent} /&gt;
    &lt;Route component={GenericNotFound} /&gt;
&lt;/Switch&gt;
```

2. Change the path (redirect) and show a 404 page:
```js
&lt;Switch&gt;
    &lt;Route path=&quot;/users&quot; component={MyComponent} /&gt;
    &lt;Redirect to=&quot;/404&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/Switch&gt;
```

